  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel your <strong>butternut squash[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and cut in half using a sharp knife</p><p>Tip: Be careful! Drizzle the knife with a little vegetable oil for easier chopping</p><p>Scoop out the seeds with a spoon and discard</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1667904786985-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1667904786985-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1667904786985-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1667904786985-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1667904786985-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut narrow slices (approx. 1cm apart) into the <strong>butternut squash halves</strong>, making sure not to cut all the way down to the base – this is your <strong>hasselback butternut squash</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>hasselback butternut squash </strong>to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>then cover tightly with <strong>tin foil</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 40 min or until the butternut squash is soft</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1667904790955-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1667904790955-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1667904790955-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1667904790955-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1667904790955-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your<strong> white wine vinegar</strong> and<strong> half </strong>your <strong>honey </strong>(save the rest for later!) in a bowl<strong> </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>– this is your <strong>honey dressing</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>pistachios</strong> and your <strong>dried cranberries</strong> finely</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped pistachios</strong> and <strong>cranberries </strong>– this is your <strong>jewel mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1667904795475-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1667904795475-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1667904795475-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1667904795475-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1667904795475-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Break your <strong>goats' cheese</strong> into rough pieces</p><p>Roll the <strong>goats' cheese pieces</strong> in the <strong>jewel mix</strong> until fully coated, then set aside for later – this is your<strong> pistachio & cranberry jewelled goats' cheese</strong></p><p>Reserve any<strong> remaining jewel mix</strong> for a garnish later</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1667904799174-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1667904799174-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1667904799174-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1667904799174-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1667904799174-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dice your <strong>‘nduja</strong> finely</p><p>Tear your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the<strong> torn ciabatta</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 6-8 min or until golden and crisp – these are your<strong> croutons</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1667904802804-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1667904802804-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1667904802804-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1667904802804-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1667904802804-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the butternut squash is softened, remove the tray from the oven and top with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>‘nduja </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and the <strong>remaining honey</strong></p><p>Return the tray to the oven and cook, uncovered, for 8-10 min further or until the 'nduja is cooked and slightly charred – this is your<strong> 'nduja butternut squash</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1667904806369-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1667904806369-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1667904806369-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1667904806369-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1667904806369-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the<strong> salad </strong>to<strong> </strong>the <strong>honey dressing </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1667904810606-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1667904810606-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
